Description: Miniature jar of uncoated coarse red siltware, with a rough base and convex sides. At the top there is a rounded rim with a slight groove below. The surface has been wet-smoothed, not very well, by hand
Bibliographic references: Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.93, p.102, p.134, p.191, pl.33)
